Hello,
I am working on friction pressure model (http://dx.doi.org/10.1088/0965-0393/20/6/065008).
The evolution PDE is given as




Based on this work, I tried to create a kernel that takes care of the friction pressure term.
switch (type)
  {

    case Residual:
    {
      return _mu[_qp] *
             ((op * op * op - op + 2.0 * _gamma[_qp] * op * SumOPj) - (3 * op * SumOPGj));
    }

    case Jacobian:
    {
      return _mu[_qp] * _phi[_j][_qp] *
             ((3.0 * op * op - 1.0 + 2.0 * _gamma[_qp] * SumOPj) - (3 * SumOPGj));
    }

    default:
      mooseError("Invalid type passed in");
  }

But I don't understand where I am going wrong. I have tried different double well functions as well, but cannot replicate the work done in this paper. How can I add pinning pressure without resolving particles?
